[div class=p 
	"This is a simple guide to the various sync settings for GB/C TASes, concerning the Gambatte core. I may do a version for Sub/GBHawk (alt. GB/C core) and BSNESv115+ (only good SGB/2 core) in the future.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=UseOfficialNintendoBootrom 
	"Use official Nintendo BootROM
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Sets whether a bootrom (or "BIOS") is used, or whether hacks are used to boot without one. If console verification or BIOS palette switching is desired, then set this to 
	[b 
		"True
	]b
	". Otherwise, setting to 
	[b 
		"True
	]b
	" is still highly recommended.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=ConsoleMode 
	"Console Mode
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Sets which console is emulated. Set this to 
	[b 
		"GBA
	]b
	" if console verification is desired. Set this to 
	[b 
		"GBA
	]b
	" or 
	[b 
		"GBC
	]b
	" if automatic colorization of GB games and/or BIOS palette switching is desired. Set this to 
	[b 
		"GBA
	]b
	" if game specific GBA enhancements are desired. Otherwise, keep this at 
	[b 
		"Auto
	]b
	".
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=MulticartCompatibility 
	"Multicart Compatibility
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Uses hacks to detect/support multicarts. Keep this to 
	[b 
		"False
	]b
	" for most games. If you are TASing a supported multicart game, set this to 
	[b 
		"True
	]b
	".
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=CartBusPullUpTime 
	"Cart Bus Pull-Up Time
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Concerns open bus emulation. Keep this at the default 
	[b 
		"8
	]b
	". Do not change this setting unless you know what you are doing.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=RealtimeRtc 
	"Realtime RTC
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Ignored for movie recordings.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=RtcDivisorOffset 
	"RTC Divisor Offset
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Concerns RTC emulation. Keep this at the default 
	[b 
		"0
	]b
	". Do not change this setting unless you know what you are doing.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=RtcOverflowHaltDaysHoursMinutesSecondsSubSeconds 
	"RTC Overflow / Halt / Days / Hours / Minutes / Seconds / Sub-Seconds
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Sets the initial internal RTC time and flags. Largely useless, as games generally reset RTC values on bootup if no save file is present. Only useful for save anchored movies.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=LatchedRtcOverflowHaltDaysHoursMinutesSeconds 
	"Latched RTC Overflow / Halt / Days / Hours / Minutes / Seconds
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Sets the initial latched RTC time and flags. Largely useless, as games generally reset RTC values on bootup if no save file is present. Only useful for save anchored movies.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=FrameLength 
	"Frame Length
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Sets the length for an input "frame". In most cases, 
	[b 
		"VBlank Driven Frames
	]b
	" should be used. If sub-frame input is desired, then 
	[b 
		"User Defined Frames
	]b
	" should be used.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=DisplayBgObjWindow 
	"Display BG / OBJ / Window
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Sets whether these graphic layers are displayed. Keep these to 
	[b 
		"True
	]b
	".
]div
